com.cyc.baseclient.datatype

Class DateConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.baseclient.datatype.DataTypeConverter<Date>
      • com.cyc.baseclient.datatype.DateConverter

  • public class DateConverter
extends DataTypeConverter<Date>

    DateConverter is designed to convert java-style dates to their corresponding CycL representations and vice versa.

    See Also:
    Date, Calendar,

      • toCycDate

        public static Naut toCycDate(Date date,
             int granularity)
        Convert the date in date to a CycL date term.
        Parameters:
        date - The date to be converted
        granularity - Indicates the desired granularity of the CycL term. Should be an int constant from this class, e.g. DateConverter.YEAR_GRANULARITY or DateConverter.SECOND_GRANULARITY.
        Returns:
        The Cyc term corresponding to date.
        Throws:
        ParseException - if date cannot be converted.
